<h2 class="sectionedit2"><a name="increasing_sound_performance_in_windows" id="increasing_sound_performance_in_windows">Increasing sound performance in Windows</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
In some cases when there are lots of sounds, Gusanos can freeze for a few seconds. We are not sure why this happens, but adding “sfx_output_mode winmm” to your <a href="doku.php?id=main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:config" class="wikilink1" title="main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:config">config.cfg</a> file seems to fix this. 
</p>

<p>
A way to test if you get this performance issue, is to catch a larpa using the manipulator in the defaut mod, hold it for around half a minute and then release it. If Gusanos stops rendering for a second or two then try the above.
</p>

</div>
